Package org.mcm.sws.wsdl

Provides a WSDL parser that makes the elements of WSDL documents available via dedicated java classes.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
Binding Abstract class to capture (service level-) binding data that can be found in all bindings
Message This class models a WSDL <Message> element (see also http://www.w3.org/TR/wsdl12)
MessageKey  
Operation This class models a WSDL <Operation> element (see also http://www.w3.org/TR/wsdl12)
OperationBinding Abstract class to capture binding data for operations
OperationKey  
Part This class models a WSDL <Part> element (see also http://www.w3.org/TR/wsdl12)
Port A port defines an individual endpoint by specifying a single address for a binding.
PortType This class models a WSDL <PortType> element (see also http://www.w3.org/TR/wsdl12)
PortTypeKey  
Service A service groups a set of related ports together (See http://www.w3.org/TR/wsdl#_services)
SOAPBinding A SOAP Binding (See http://www.w3.org/TR/wsdl#_soap-b)
SOAPBodyDef This class captures the information of the soap:body element.
SOAPFragmentDef Captures the information stored in soap:header, soap:body, soap:headerfault elements in the soap binding/operation/input, binding/operation/output and binding/operation/fault elements.
SOAPHeaderDef Represents info of the soap:header element; it allows header to be defined that are transmitted inside the Header element of the SOAP Envelope.
SOAPOperationBinding Holds the SOAP specific information of an operation in binding if the binding used is SOAP.
VariableKey  
WSDLDocument This class models the WSDL <Definitions> root-element (see also http://www.w3.org/TR/wsdl12) and provides a parser method.
XSDTypeKey  
 

Exception Summary
WSDLParserException Exception thrown during WSDL parsing.
 

Package org.mcm.sws.wsdl Description

Provides a WSDL parser that makes the elements of WSDL documents available via dedicated java classes.
